  "referred_to_by": [
    {
      "type": "LinguisticObject",
      "content": "This is a set of five graduated block-and-tackle configurations mounted on a frame, demonstrating mechanical advantage from 1:1 through 5:1. Each tackle adds one more supporting rope segment and one more pulley, progressively showing the **\"golden rule of mechanics\"**: what is gained in force is lost in distance. The apparatus belongs to a **three-part pedagogical series** of pulley demonstrations in the Teylers Fysisch Kabinet (FK 0018 → FK 0020 → FK 0022), progressing from individual pulleys to assembled blocks to complete graduated tackle systems. All three date to 1775–1799 and derive from designs by **Willem Jacob 's Gravesande** (1688–1742).",
